IN A BIZARRE turn of events, a Mitchells Plain resident staged her own kidnapping and demanded a R10 million ransom just to prove that her family loved her dearly.Police spokesperson FC van Wyk said the woman s husband reported to police that he last saw his wife on January 4 at 09.20am after she told him she was headed to the town centre in Mitchells Plain. An exchange deal was negotiated with the alleged kidnappers. Mitchells Plain detectives were deployed near a fast food outlet at the Promenade Mall, Van Wyk said. When they spotted her at the mall, she started running but was arrested at AZ Berman Drive, Lentegeur. The victim was interviewed by the investigating officer and it came to light that she wanted to see if her family loves her. No other suspects were involved, said Van Wyk.He said after the woman left she had sent WhatsApp messages to her daughter pretending to be kidnappers who said should the family want to see her alive again, they must pay a ransom. Her cellphone was then switched off. Van Wyk said detectives then set up a temporary Joint Operational Centre in the boardroom of Mitchells Plain Police Station. Van Wyk said Grabber technology was used to trace the cellphone of the victim to find her location. She was arrested and charged with kidnapping, extortion and defeating the ends of justice, and appeared in the Mitchells Plain Magistrate s Court yesterday.